> Firecracker sauce is one of our most beloved sauces (and we have a ton of sauces!) It's sweet, spicy, savory, and really has it all.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Toss
on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.
Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

Meanwhile, in a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water
(2 1/4 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover
and reduce heat to low.

Cook, covered, until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until
ready to serve.

While rice cooks, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Trim and thinly slice
@button mushrooms{8%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Peel and
mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb} until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4 servings). Trim
and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Once carrots have roasted ~{10%minutes}, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully
toss green beans on empty side of sheet with a drizzle of @oil{}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. Return sheet to top rack and roast until veggies are lightly browned
and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== Firecracker Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @vegan mayo{4%tablespoon}, @Sriracha{1%teaspoon}
(use less if you prefer less heat), 1 TBSP @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon},
1 tsp @rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, and 1⁄2 tsp @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}
(2 TBSP sweet soy glaze, 2 tsp vinegar, and 1 tsp sugar for 4 servings).

> Be sure to measure the vinegar—we sent more!

Add water 1 tsp at a time until sauce reaches a drizzling consistency. Taste and
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside until ready to serve.

== Mushrooms ==

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{5%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and slightly
crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium; stir in minced ginger, scallion whites, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon},
and a drizzle of oil. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Remove pan from heat and stir in remaining sweet soy glaze until mushrooms are
evenly coated. Cover to keep warm.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with carrots, green beans, and mushrooms in
separate sections. Drizzle bowls with firecracker sauce and garnish with
scallion greens and @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}. Serve.